S_0
For\ the\ sets\ S_i\ where\ i,j = 0,1,2,...,n\ and\ s_i \in S_i\  where\ s_i \in \mathbb{N}.
S_i \cap S_j = \emptyset,\ for\ any\ and\ all\ considered\ sets,
and\ |S_0| = |S_1| = |S_2|...|S_i| = M\ where\ M\ is\ the\ cardinality\ of\ any\ set\ S_i.
In\ addition,\ for\ all\ sets,\  S_i\ =\ \left\{i, i+1, i+2,...,i+M - 1\right\}. 
Let\ x \in \mathbb{N},
\ x \in S_i\ if\ and\ only\ if
x/M = i + k/M\ where\ k\ is\ the\ remainder\ of\ the\ quotient.
S_0
x/4\ =\ 0 + j/4,\ where\ 0\ \leq\ j\ < 4.
x = 10
x/4 = 2 + 2/4
x = 10\ is\ a\ member\ of\ the\ set\ S_2\ as\ i = 2.
